Another accident has happened in Ngcobo this evening, no fatalities were reported. A minibus traveling from Mqanduli to Cape Town has overturned on the R61 road near Cocklein in Ngcobo. Department of health spokesman Sizwe Kupelo said the taxi had 13 people on board. “Two of them are in a critical condition, five serious and others in a stable condition,” he said. Kupelo said the survivors would be taken to hospital. Earlier today, a bus traveling from Welkom in the Free State overturned in Satan’s Neck, killing 12 people on the scene. 